# 5. N-Queens Problem

* Place N queens on an N×N chessboard.
* No two queens should attack each other.
* Queens cannot share:

  * Row
  * Column
  * Diagonal
* Solved using backtracking.
* Queens are placed row by row.

The N-Queens problem is a classic backtracking problem where queens must be placed safely on a chessboard.
The algorithm checks whether a queen placement is valid before moving forward. If conflict occurs, it 
removes the queen and tries another position. This process continues until all queens are placed correctly.

### Example

4-Queens Solution:

```id="szokdy"
. Q . .
. . . Q
Q . . .
. . Q .
```

