# 8. Permutations and Combinations

* Permutation means arrangement of elements.
* Combination means selection of elements.
* Permutations consider order.
* Combinations ignore order.
* Solved using recursion and backtracking.
* Used in probability and algorithms.

Permutations and combinations are important mathematical concepts used in algorithm design. Backtracking generates 
all possible arrangements and selections recursively. These problems improve logical thinking and are commonly asked 
in coding interviews and competitive programming.

### Example

