# 9. Subset Generation

* Generates all subsets of a set.
* Also called Power Set.
* Total subsets = 2ⁿ.
* Uses include/exclude method.
* Solved using recursion and backtracking.
* Useful in optimization problems.

Subset generation creates all possible subsets of a given set. The algorithm recursively decides whether to include or exclude
an element. This technique is widely used in combinational and dynamic programming problems. It helps understand recursion 
trees and search spaces effectively.

### Example

For {1,2}

```id="qugklt"
{}
{1}
{2}
{1,2}
```
